Name: In the Stardew of the Valley
Author: Patchier#6969
Description:
In the Stardew of the Valley....that I loved best. 

This is a small, stable, and (hopefully) enjoyable modlist built around the very popular "Stardew Valley Expanded" mod, which, as it's name suggests, greatly expands Stardew Valley in ways that feel very, VERY organic to the base game.

State.Name: PPJA - Cannabis Kit
State.Author: taintedwheat and Project Populate Json Assets
State.Description: Mayor Lewis has recently passed legislation allowing you to now grow cannabis on your farm! Adds new craftables and recipes as well as a new crop! This mod is a re-release of my previous cannabis crop mod, but with an overhaul.

State.Name: PPJA - Fresh Meat_An 'Alternative' Butcher Mod
State.Author: Project Populate Json Assets
State.Description: Sure, you can grow-up your cows and slaughter them but what about a plant alternative?

State.Name: Museum Expansion
State.Author: andril11 and a lot of people
State.Description: This is a complete museum lore expansion! Adding new npcs, shops and more to come!

Archives.Name: Ancient Crops - Custom Icons - BAGI Add-On-4472-1-0-1-1568605329.zip

State.Name: PPJA - Ancient Crops
State.Author: Project Populate Json Assets
State.Description: Since you've had luck growing an ancient seed, let's see how your green thumb treats these ancient crops.

State.Name: PPJA - Artisan Valley
State.Author: Project Populate Json Assets
State.Description: Me sell artisan goods. Okay, poke? Bring coines. 20 New Machines and 150+ New Items!

State.Name: Better Artisan Good Icons
State.Author: Cat
State.Description: This mod makes jelly, pickles, wine, juice, and honey icons be based on the fruit, vegetable, or flower used to make them. Easily tell at a glance what types of wine, jelly, etc you have in your inventory! (You can hide the little icons if you want too :))

State.Name: Custom Cask Mod
State.Author: Digus
State.Description: Adds a way to customize the casks. It comes configurable with Pickles and Maple Syrup but can be changed to add any 'Object' and change the time of the products that already work on casks. You can also enable casks to work outside the cellar.

State.Name: Multi Yield Crops
State.Author: Cherry
State.Description: Allows crops to yield more than one kind of harvest. Fully configurable and with content pack support

State.Name: PPJA Icon Pack for Better Artisan Goods Icons
State.Author: Project Populate Json Assets
State.Description: A content pack for Better Artisan Goods Icons that is meant to pair with the PPJA collection. Includes optional download for default crops & Stardrops Crop as well.

State.Name: Seasonal Outfits for SVE (Vanilla Style)
State.Author: Poltergeister and Tanpoponoko
State.Description: Gives the NPCs of Stardew Valley Expanded seasonal clothing.

State.Name: TimeSpeed
State.Author: cantorsdust
State.Description: Control the flow of time in the game: speed it up, slow it down, or freeze it altogether. This can happen automatically or when you press a key in the game.

State.Name: Traveling Takes Time
State.Author: Vrakyas
State.Description: Traveling by mine cart or bus will take some time

State.Name: Quest Framework
State.Author: PurrplingCat
State.Description: Framework for work with quests like create custom quests, define custom quest types and handle quests.

State.Name: NPC Adventures (It's time to adventure)
State.Author: PurrplingCat
State.Description: It's time to adventure! Go on an adventure with the villagers from Pelican Town as companions!

State.Name: Tell Everyone (Town Gossip)
State.Author: LemurKat
State.Description:
Caught the Mayor in a scandalous act and declared you're going to "Tell everyone" but disappointed because nothing comes of it?

Well now it can!

At least for three days.

State.Name: Anti-Social NPCs
State.Author: Super Aardvark
State.Description: Allows modders to create NPCs that the player can't befriend.

State.Name: Farm Type Manager (FTM)
State.Author: Esca-MMC
State.Description: Farm Type Manager is a spawning framework that allows players and modders to spawn customizable features from Stardew's farm types. It can automatically create forage, ore, monsters, and large objects (stumps, boulders, meteors, etc) at any location in the game.

State.Name: Json Assets
State.Author: spacechase0
State.Description: Successor to Custom Crops.

State.Name: Mail Framework Mod
State.Author: Digus
State.Description: Framework to use the in game mailbox. Console commands to adjust the mail. Code and Content Pack interfaces.

State.Name: Custom Crafting Stations
State.Author: Cherry
State.Description: Allows modders to add customized crafting stations which opens menus with a limited selection of recipes, without those recipes cluttering up the vanilla crafting menus

State.Name: Expanded Preconditions Utility
State.Author: Cherry
State.Description: A utility mod built on top of the game's preconditions system to offer a conditions system any mod can use

State.Name: Winter Grass
State.Author: Cat
State.Description: This mod makes grass survive through winter!

State.Name: Producer Framework Mod
State.Author: Digus
State.Description: Framework to add custom rules for producing objects. Supports code and content pack interfaces.

State.Name: Dynamic Night Time
State.Author: KNakamura
State.Description: This mod gives Stardew Valley a more dynamic daylight cycle, changing when it gets dark and adding a dawn period at the start of the day. It also adds a full light cycle, adding sunrise and sunset effects. These times will vary depending on the time of year. Can be configured to match your latitude. Does not alter start time.

State.Name: Stardew Valley Expanded
State.Author: FlashShifter
State.Description: Stardew Valley Expanded is a fanmade expansion for ConcernedApe's Stardew Valley. This mod features 23 new locations, 126 new character events, 9 new NPCs, a new village, 750 location messages, reimagined maps and festivals (all maps), a huge remastered farm map, a new world map reflecting all changes, and many miscellaneous additions!

Archives.Name: NPC Map Locations for Stardew Valley Expanded-239-2-5-11-1597472731.zip

State.Name: NPC Map Locations
State.Author: Bouhm
State.Description: Shows the locations of NPC and farmers on the map page and on a minimap. Provides modified map pages that are much more accurate to the game.

State.Name: SpaceCore
State.Author: spacechase0
State.Description: Required by a few mods.

State.Name: Stardew Valley Expanded
State.Author: FlashShifter
State.Description: Stardew Valley Expanded is a fanmade expansion for ConcernedApe's Stardew Valley. This mod features 23 new locations, 126 new character events, 9 new NPCs, a new village, 750 location messages, reimagined maps and festivals (all maps), a huge remastered farm map, a new world map reflecting all changes, and many miscellaneous additions!

State.Name: Shop Tile Framework
State.Author: Cherry
State.Description: A Framework mod that allows modders to add custom shops to the game, as well as edit vanilla shops

State.Name: Climates of Ferngill
State.Author: Sakorona
State.Description: This mod expands the climate system to be more robust, adding custom weathers. This climate system can be tweaked to add a degree of difficulty to the game.

State.Name: PyTK - Platonymous Toolkit
State.Author: Platonymous
State.Description: Toolkit for Smapi Mods

State.Name: Lunar Disturbances
State.Author: Sakorona
State.Description: This mod adds a moon overhead, which enables events such as a solar eclipse, a blood moon for rare occasions, and more items washed up or less.

State.Name: Hybrid Crop Engine
State.Author: spacechase0
State.Description: Fully grown adjacent crops can have a chance of having a hybrid crop appear in between them.

State.Name: Lookup Anything
State.Author: Pathoschild
State.Description: See live info about whatever's under your cursor when you press F1. Learn a villager's favourite gifts, when a crop will be ready to harvest, how long a fence will last, why your farm animals are unhappy, and more.

State.Name: PPJA - Ancient Crops
State.Author: Project Populate Json Assets
State.Description: Since you've had luck growing an ancient seed, let's see how your green thumb treats these ancient crops.

State.Name: PPJA - Fantasy Crops
State.Author: Project Populate Json Assets
State.Description: A handful of fantasy-style crops for your farm.

State.Name: PPJA - Fruits and Veggies
State.Author: Project Populate Json Assets
State.Description: Mizu's crop sprites are now able to be used with JsonAssets.

State.Name: Shaved Ice and Frozen Treats
State.Author: Hadi and Zosa and Fwippy
State.Description: Everyone knows there's no such thing as TOO much ice cream... so here's 26 new recipes and a Shaved Ice Machine for good measure.

State.Name: Artisanal Soda Makers
State.Author: Hadi
State.Description: Tired of waiting to complete your Community Center before you can stick it to The Man? Do you really, REALLY, like soft drinks, and wish Joja Cola would come in better, snootier flavors? If so, I present a set of Soda Makers, for all your hipster soda needs.

State.Name: Artisanal Soda Makers
State.Author: Hadi
State.Description: Tired of waiting to complete your Community Center before you can stick it to The Man? Do you really, REALLY, like soft drinks, and wish Joja Cola would come in better, snootier flavors? If so, I present a set of Soda Makers, for all your hipster soda needs.

State.Name: Fizzy Drinks
State.Author: MelindaC and Fwippy
State.Description: An offshoot of Artisanal Soda Makers, this mod focuses on specialty pop drinks. Based on RL sodas, this mod introduces four new foraging items, two new trees, two new crops and over fifty new products to your crafting experiences.

State.Name: Automate
State.Author: Pathoschild
State.Description: Place a chest next to a machine (like a furnace or crystalarium), and the machine will automatically pull raw items from the chest and push processed items into it. Connect multiple machines with a chest to link them.

State.Name: Challenging Community Center Bundles (for PPJA)
State.Author: Alja
State.Description: A bundle overhaul mod which utilizes the new crops, fruits and maschines provided by PPJA and tries to create a challenging but not frustrating experience playing Stardew Valley.

State.Name: Content Patcher
State.Author: Pathoschild
State.Description: Loads content packs that change the game's images and data without replacing XNB files.

State.Name: PPJA - Khadija's Recipe Shop
State.Author: Project Populate Json Assets
State.Description: A new pair of vendors have set up shop in the valley, and they're bringing an ever expanding selection of exotic goods to Pelican Town! Buy cooking recipes and ingredients from Zamir on weekdays, and check out Nasira's collection of weapons and fancy new crafting recipes on Weekends! Sell JA items in an organized, balanced, and lore-friendly way!

State.Name: Seasonal Villager Outfits
State.Author: Tanpopnoko and ParadigmNomad
State.Description: An outfit for every season!

State.Name: TMXL Map Toolkit
State.Author: Platonymous
State.Description:
Toolkit for adding/editing/replacing maps and creating buildables.

(Formerly named TMXLoader).

State.Name: A Better Backyard - For SVE Immersive Farm 2
State.Author: LilyMods
State.Description: This mod seeks to improve upon the backyard that is behind your farm house, with SVE - IF2 ReMastered, by increasing the amount of locations that would otherwise be perfect for construction if not for a few design flaws. Optionally revamps the Immersive Farm's established Shed to be in a more accessible location with a warmer interior.
